I had afternoon tea there. Great value for money. 60% off. No charge for tea. No charge for hot sauce. No service charge. The food is good and the portion is big by HK standard. Cost us only $65 per person. The place is nice and comfortable. Afternoon tea starts at 2:30pm. Highly recommended.

Delicious food and good service. You can get dim sum here that is more unique than others. The venue is also orderly and clean. Food tastes very clean and comes out quick. A very busy location as it is in Times square.
Value for money if you are going for the morning tea session.
Variety of food is great.  Food taste goo

result.name: Chung's Kitchen

reviews.text: 12品で88香港ドルのお得な宮廷皇品盤をオーダー。1人で食べるのに嬉しい品数と丁度いい量で、かつ料理が美味しく、満足度が高い。ただし最初にオーダーするポットのお茶は40香港ドルと高め。店員は皆気さくで優しく居心地がいい。
要預約，午市祗是給顧客一時三十分鐘，食品可以，点心，炒粉麵。出名魚頭煲，但經常沽清。
超抵食，食物質素保證，上菜快，坐得舒服，環境好好，服務好
星期一至五飲早茶，價錢平，食物佳，仲要免茶錢！

absolutely rip off. had our tea wrong, missed rice, wrong veggie... very unprofessional. overly salty roast goose.
the only good thing is the location, decor and aircon.
